cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with dense reconstruction from a moving camera, which is a problem in computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a probabilistic approach, which involves modeling uncertainties and estimating probabilities, making it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses both spatial and temporal correlations, which suggests relevance to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.GR (Graphics).
